category: WORDS READ BACKWARDS
category comment: 

clue: A ruminant races backwards & becomes this last name of actor Oliver & musician Lou

response: Reed (from deer)

clue: Read backwards, a Japanese word for dried seaweed becomes this metal

response: iron (from nori)

clue: A word preceding "chart" for a step-by-step guide becomes this big canine

response: wolf (from flow)

clue: A set of enzymes from a cow's stomach lining becomes this, slang for what might buy you a plate of fish & chips

response: tenner (from rennet)

clue: A runner who sets the tempo of a race rewinds & becomes this shortened word for a TV opening that might begin "previously on"

response: a recap (from pacer)

